One person has been killed while another remains on life support at the Charlotte Maxeke Hospital. JOHANNESBURG Four people have been arrested in connection with a shooting in Sandton in the early hours of Monday morning.One person has been killed while another remains on life support at the Charlotte Maxeke Hospital. Police say he was shot in the head.Spokesperson David Mothapo says an altercation between a group of people lead to the shooting. The suspect produced a firearm and shot at the two victims. The suspect then fled the scene together with a woman in a vehicle. The two victims were immediately rushed hospital where one victim was later declared dead. #SandtonShooting The four people will be charged with murder and attempted murder later this morning. ML